abstract: World Cup books are a tougher sell when a key character — the United States national team — is missing.
snippet: World Cup books are a tougher sell when a key character — the United States national team — is missing.
lead_paragraph: It is not often that a drunk man in red shorts and a blue blazer with white stars turns up at a book reading, and probably less often when he is thrown out for repeatedly standing up to interrupt the speakers while holding aloft a flag representing the Premier League club Crystal Palace. Then again, most book readings don’t double as podcast tapings, or take place in front of a boisterous crowd of admirers in a New York live music venue.
